cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on using computer vision techniques to model visual reasoning on the Raven's Progressive Matrices test, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of generative models also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) categories. Finally, the discussion of sociocultural backgrounds and their impact on test performance suggests that the paper may also fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) category.
